instruction:
Let $f(x) = 1 / (1 + x^{2})$. On the interval $-5 \leq x \leq 5$, with $n = 10$, estimate the error between the values of $I_{h}(x)$ at the midpoint of each node and $f(x)$ as _____.

Options:
A. $$
\mid R_{1} ( x ) \mid\leq\frac{1} {2} \, h^{3}
$$
B. $$
\mid R_{1} ( x ) \mid\leq\frac{1} {8} \, h^{3}
$$
C. $$
\mid R_{1} ( x ) \mid\geq\frac{1} {4} \, h^{3}
$$
D. $$
\mid R_{1} ( x ) \mid\leq\frac{1} {3} \, h^{2}
$$
E. $$
\mid R_{1} ( x ) \mid\geq\frac{1} {5} \, h^{2}
$$
F. $$
\mid R_{1} ( x ) \mid\geq\frac{1} {2} \, h^{2}
$$
G. $$
\mid R_{1} ( x ) \mid\leq\frac{1} {10} \, h^{2}
$$
H. $$
\mid R_{1} ( x ) \mid\leq\frac{1} {4} \, h^{2}
$$
I. $$
\mid R_{1} ( x ) \mid\leq\frac{1} {6} \, h^{4}
$$
J. $$
\mid R_{1} ( x ) \mid\geq\frac{1} {3} \, h^{5}
$$
